<span style=\"font-size: 75%;\">(variants)</span>\n|\u2014\n|-\n|#2<ref>{{cite web|title=Tales from Harrow County: Death's Choir #2|url=https://www.darkhorse.com/Comics/3004-147/Tales-from-Harrow-County-Deaths-Choir-2|website=DarkHorse.com|publisher=Dark Horse Comics|accessdate=31 October 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Tales from Harrow County: Death's Choir #2 (Tyler Crook variant cover)|url=https://www.darkhorse.com/Comics/3006-424/Tales-from-Harrow-County-Deaths-Choir-2-Tyler-Crook-Variant-Cover|website=DarkHorse.com|publisher=Dark Horse Comics|accessdate=31 October 2019}}</ref>\n|January 15, 2020\n|TBD\n|-\n|#3\n|February 12, 2020\n|TBD\n|-\n|#4\n|March 11, 2020\n|TBD\n|}\n\n===Trade paperbacks===\nFour months after each arc of ''Harrow County'' wrapped up, it was collected in trade paperback.\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align: center\"\n|-\n!colspan=6|Trade paperbacks\n|-\n!Volume\n!Title\n!Release Date\n!Material collected\n!Extras\n!ISBN\n|-\n|colspan=6 style=background:#bc4026|\n|-\n|1\n|''Harrow County:<br>Countless Haints''<ref>{{cite web|title=Harrow County \u2013 Volume 1: Countless Haints|url=http://www.darkhorse.com/Books/26-617/Harrow-County-Volume-1-Countless-Haints-TPB|website=DarkHorse.com|publisher=Dark Horse Comics|accessdate=15 October 2015}}</ref>\n|December 2, 2015\n|''Harrow County'' #1\u20134\n|\n* 24-page sketchbook\n* The original ''Countless Haints'' prose story from Cullen Bunn's blog\n|{{ISBNT|9781616557805}}\n|-\n|colspan=6 style=background:#dda628|\n|-\n|2\n|''Harrow County:<br>Twice Told''<ref>{{cite web|title=Harrow County \u2013 Volume 2: Twice Told|url=http://www.darkhorse.com/Books/26-618/Harrow-County-Volume-2-Twice-Told-TPB|website=DarkHorse.com|publisher=Dark Horse Comics|accessdate=17 December 2015}}</ref>\n|April 13, 2016\n|''Harrow County'' #5\u20138\n|\n* 17-page sketchbook\n|{{ISBNT|9781616559007}}\n|-\n|colspan=6 style=background:#b5b59d|\n|-\n|3\n|''Harrow County:<br>Snake Doctor''<ref>{{cite web|title=Har